<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 3:33PM MDT  by NWS Billings</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Carter
County through 415 PM MDT...
At 333 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Ridgeway, or 28 miles south of Ekalaka, moving east at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Ridgeway.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
